  "prompt": "Are there really New Yorkers as neurotic as Woody Allen is in his movies?",
  "response": "While Woody Allen's characters are often exaggerated for comedic effect, they do reflect certain stereotypical New York personality traits. Some New Yorkers can be neurotic, anxious, and intellectually self-conscious, particularly in certain professional and social circles. However, not all New Yorkers are like the characters in Allen's films. His portrayals are stylized and comedic representations that draw on real personality types but amplify them for dramatic and humorous effect. New York is an incredibly diverse city with people from many different backgrounds and personality types, so it would be an oversimplification to say that all or even most New Yorkers are as neurotic as his movie characters.",
